text.section:
The provisions of this subtitle that apply to insurers also apply to:
a corporation that operates a nonprofit health service plan under Title 14, Subtitle 1 of this article;
an insurer that is doing or has done insurance business in the State and against whom claims arising from that insurance business may exist now or in the future;
a person that purports to do insurance business in the State;
an insurer that has an insured resident or located in the State;
a person organized or in the process of organizing with intent to do insurance business in the State; and
a person that does, or has done, any of the acts of an insurance business specified in § 4-205 of this article.
